                <h1>Roberto Clemente: The Legendary Humanitarian and Baseball Icon</h1>
                <p>Roberto Clemente was a Puerto Rican baseball legend, renowned for both his exceptional skills and humanitarian efforts. A Hall of Fame outfielder for the Pittsburgh Pirates, he won 2,305 hits, 12 Gold Gloves, and two World Series titles. Tragically, Clemente died in a plane crash while delivering aid to Nicaragua in 1972.</p>
